<br>
     Ghosting and plugging are too additional ways of hacking but are not looked upon with the frowning eye like the other type of hacking is.<br>
<br>
     1) Ghosting can best be explained in that &quot;meaolil&quot; is at one end of a zone and wants to get to the other side without getting in a fight.  Meaolil actually will unplug the internet connection which causes a break in the system and then Meaolil will start running across the zone while watching the linkdead meter....while running across zone, meaolil is impervious to damage because the computer believes that meaolil is still at the start of the zone and nothing has updated.  Just prior to going Linkdead, meaolil will then replug the connection and everything will start catching up with him.<br>
<br>
     2) Plugging is pretty simple, you unplug the computer in order to avoid the death.  I've been told by a gm that plugging is actually frowned upon and can be used as a game infraction against the plugger, but they also said it's very hard to prove someone plugging when they are in the midst of zoning.<br>
<br>
     I personally have not plugged, ghosted or hacked... but there are some ways that you can bug track and can also make it seem you are ghosting when in fact you are not.<br>
<br>
     1) One way that may bug track is to run around in a circle several times so it looks like you are in several areas around the same spot.  I've seen people also run backwards in a circle to do the same thing.  And it seems to work, but not always.<br>
    <br>
     2) On the ghosting issue... I recently learned a technique where as you are running forward you also have the character &quot;bounce&quot; move to the left or right or back and forth between left and right.  You are basically running forward and to the right or left at the same time, but you are doing the right and left moves by tapping them out instead of doing it in a steady manner.  You can still be hit by someone coming after you from behind, but you won't get hit as often and the person chasing you will see you bouncing in front of him.  When he can't hit you like he normally would, it appears you are ghosting.<br>
<br>
     I'm sure there are other &quot;tricks&quot; of the trade and I'd love to see others post them if possible.<br>
  <p>Ravenwolf Pureheart, 55th Season Outrider of Tunare<br>
